The paper deals with deep neural networks for image denoising, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of the denoising performance, which involves optimization and information theory (cs.IT). The use of neural networks for denoising is a popular application of machine learning (cs.LG), and the paper specifically focuses on generative models (cs.NE) and autoencoders (cs.AI).
